content:
When setting up a Messaging channel in Service Cloud, it's helpful to understand the terms that we use to talk about messaging in Salesforce.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
This article applies to:	Messaging for In-App, Messaging for Web, standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel

TERM	DEFINITION
Asynchronous	Messaging sessions can be started, stopped, then re-engaged at any time. Closing the messaging window doesnâ€™t delete the conversation history.
Channel	A way for customers to exchange messages with your business. Salesforce supports these channel types in Messaging: Facebook Messenger, WhatsApp, Apple Messages for Business, SMS, Messaging for In-App, Messaging for Web, and Bring Your Own Channel.

Conversation	A conversation includes one or more messaging sessions associated with a single messaging user. Messaging offers asynchronous, persistent conversations that store all messaging history.
Conversation Channel Definition	An entity in Salesforce that contains metadata for any Bring Your Own Channel integration.
Messaging Component	Structured content that agents can send to customers in a messaging session to share or gather information.
Messaging Session	An exchange of one or more messages between your business and a customer that takes place over a Messaging channel. Messaging sessions end differently depending on your channel and device.

Messaging User	A record representing a user who communicates with your company over a particular channel, such as Facebook Messenger.
Parameter Mapping	A way to map standard and custom parameters to flows or agent tasks.
Persistent	Conversation history remains in the conversation window after the conversation is over.
Pre-Chat Fields	A way to collect customer details before an agent starts a conversation in a Messaging for In-App and Web channel.
Proactive Messaging	Messaging sessions initiated by an agent or automation in Salesforce, for example, an agent messages a customer in your WhatsApp channel, or a flow or process sends an automatic notification or broadcast.

Routing	The logic that determines how customer inquiries in a Messaging channel are routed. The Salesforce routing tool is Omni-Channel.
title: Service Cloud Messaging Glossary
